text: Sheridan County School District #1 is a public school district based in Ranchester, Wyoming, United States. ==Geography== Sheridan County School District #1 serves the western portion of Sheridan County, including the following communities: *Incorporated places **Town of Dayton **Town of Ranchester *Census-designated places (Note: All census-designated places are unincorporated.) **Big Horn **Parkman ==Schools== ===Secondary schools=== *Grades 9-12 **Tongue River High School *Grades 6-12 **Big Horn Middle/High School *Grades 6-8 **Tongue River Middle School ===Elementary schools=== *Grades K-5''' **Big Horn Elementary School **Tongue River Elementary School *Grades K-4 **Slack Elementary School ==Student demographics== The following figures are as of October 1, 2009. *Total District Enrollment: 923 *Student enrollment by gender **Male: 464 (50.27%) **Female: 459 (49.73%) *Student enrollment by ethnicity **American Indian or Alaska Native: 43 (4.66%) **Black or African American: 1 (0.11%) **Hispanic or Latino: 41 (4.44%) **Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander: 2 (0.22%) **Two or More Races: 9 (0.98%) **White: 827 (89.60%) ==See also== *List of school districts in Wyoming ==References== ==External links== *Sheridan County School District #1 – official site.
